Seriously this is the best Popeyes in Brooklyn! If you are in the mood for Popeyes go to this location. I live 5 blocks from a Popeyes location in Bayridge, but I choose to travel 40 blocks to this one. I also choose this location if I order from seamless/grubhub . It is 50 blocks further than the one right near my apartment, yet the food is ALWAYS way better quality and way hotter. The staff is awesome, they actually take the time to listen and accommodate any special requests. The one gentleman that works there , I think his name is Z is really the best !!!! I wanted to take the time to write a review because he does a great job and ALWAYS had a great attitude! Thank you cuzzo!

I would give them four stars but they're usually understaffed. I definitely would not name this establishment a "fast food joint". I like the chicken, but on rare occasions I've experienced stomach discomfort after consuming it. I wonder if it has to do to with them not changing the oil on a regular basis. Although I have to say, most restaurants apply this practice as well. Noticed a roach on the wall once. Management's response was lackadaisical.

We brought it back to the location and got a refund and showed the manager.  We no longer eat from Popeyes. Check your food before you eat or just go some where else!

I was excited when I learned there would be a new Popeyes opening near my location, and it did not disappoint me. Actually, this store is the best Popeyes branch I have ever been at. The chicken is always good (though I have only ever ordered wings, which is my Popeyes favorite), the store is clean and neat, and the staff are nice and polite. Here's hope their good service can last long when they are no longer a new store.
